title: Independent sets in a Moore system

blocks.name: mrisval
blocks.content: Value of the set of independent sets of a Moore system. (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)
blocks.origin:
thm mrisval(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3) {

  -| wceq(c3, cfv(cmrc, c0))

  -| diffsc(s0, c1)
  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
} = {
  eqtrd(c2, crab(s0, cpw(c1), wral(s1, cv(s0), wn(wcel(cv(s1), cfv(c3, cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1)))))))), crab(s0, cpw(cuni(c0)), wral(s1, cv(s0), wn(wcel(cv(s1), cfv(c3, cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1)))))))), wcel(c0, cfv(cmre, c1)))

  sseli(c0, cfv(cmre, c1), cuni(crn(cmre)))
  fvssunirn(cmre, c1)
  fvmpt3i(hs0, c0, cuni(crn(cmre)), cmri, crab(s0, cpw(cuni(c0)), wral(s1, cv(s0), wn(wcel(cv(s1), cfv(c3, cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1)))))))), crab(s0, cpw(cuni(cv(hs0))), wral(s1, cv(s0), wn(wcel(cv(s1), cfv(cfv(cmrc, cv(hs0)), cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1)))))))))

  pweqd(cuni(cv(hs0)), cuni(c0), wceq(cv(hs0), c0))
  unieq(cv(hs0), c0)
  ralbidv(s1, cv(s0), wceq(cv(hs0), c0), wn(wcel(cv(s1), cfv(cfv(cmrc, cv(hs0)), cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1)))))), wn(wcel(cv(s1), cfv(c3, cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1)))))))
  notbid(wceq(cv(hs0), c0), wcel(cv(s1), cfv(cfv(cmrc, cv(hs0)), cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1))))), wcel(cv(s1), cfv(c3, cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1))))))
  eleq2d(cv(s1), cfv(cfv(cmrc, cv(hs0)), cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1)))), cfv(c3, cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1)))), wceq(cv(hs0), c0))
  fveq1d(cfv(cmrc, cv(hs0)), cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1))), c3, wceq(cv(hs0), c0))
  syl6eqr(cfv(cmrc, cv(hs0)), c3, cfv(cmrc, c0), wceq(cv(hs0), c0))
  fveq2(cv(hs0), c0, cmrc)
  df-mri(hs0, s0, s1)
  rabex(s0, cpw(cuni(cv(hs0))), wral(s1, cv(s0), wn(wcel(cv(s1), cfv(cfv(cmrc, cv(hs0)), cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1))))))))
  pwex(cuni(cv(hs0)))
  vuniex(hs0)
  rabeqdv(s0, cpw(cuni(c0)), cpw(c1), wcel(c0, cfv(cmre, c1)), wral(s1, cv(s0), wn(wcel(cv(s1), cfv(c3, cdif(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1))))))))
  pweqd(cuni(c0), c1, wcel(c0, cfv(cmre, c1)))

thm mrisval(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3) {
  ‚ä¢ (c0 ‚àà(Moore ` c1)‚Üí c2 = { s0 ‚àà P(c1)| ‚àÄ(s1 ‚àà s0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà(c3 `(s0 \ { s1 })))})
  ‚ä£ c3 =(mrCls ` c0)
  ‚ä£ c2 =(mrInd ` c0)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, s1)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, c0)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, c1)
  ‚ä£ d(s1, c0)
} = {
  eqtrd(c2, { s0 ‚àà P(c1)| ‚àÄ(s1 ‚àà s0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà(c3 `(s0 \ { s1 })))}, { s0 ‚àà P(‚ãÉ c0)| ‚àÄ(s1 ‚àà s0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà(c3 `(s0 \ { s1 })))}, c0 ‚àà(Moore ` c1))
  syl5eq(c2, { s0 ‚àà P(‚ãÉ c0)| ‚àÄ(s1 ‚àà s0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà(c3 `(s0 \ { s1 })))}, (mrInd ` c0), c0 ‚àà(Moore ` c1))
  syl(c0 ‚àà(Moore ` c1), (mrInd ` c0)= { s0 ‚àà P(‚ãÉ c0)| ‚àÄ(s1 ‚àà s0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà(c3 `(s0 \ { s1 })))}, c0 ‚àà ‚ãÉ ran(Moore))
  sseli(c0, (Moore ` c1), ‚ãÉ ran(Moore))
  fvssunirn(cmre, c1)
  fvmpt3i(hs0, c0, ‚ãÉ ran(Moore), cmri, { s0 ‚àà P(‚ãÉ c0)| ‚àÄ(s1 ‚àà s0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà(c3 `(s0 \ { s1 })))}, { s0 ‚àà P(‚ãÉ hs0)| ‚àÄ(s1 ‚àà s0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà((mrCls ` hs0)`(s0 \ { s1 })))})
  rabeqbidv(s0, P(‚ãÉ hs0), P(‚ãÉ c0), hs0 = c0, ‚àÄ(s1 ‚àà s0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà((mrCls ` hs0)`(s0 \ { s1 }))), ‚àÄ(s1 ‚àà s0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà(c3 `(s0 \ { s1 }))))
  pweqd(‚ãÉ hs0, ‚ãÉ c0, hs0 = c0)
  unieq(hs0, c0)
  ralbidv(s1, s0, hs0 = c0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà((mrCls ` hs0)`(s0 \ { s1 })), ¬¨ s1 ‚àà(c3 `(s0 \ { s1 })))
  notbid(hs0 = c0, s1 ‚àà((mrCls ` hs0)`(s0 \ { s1 })), s1 ‚àà(c3 `(s0 \ { s1 })))
  eleq2d(s1, ((mrCls ` hs0)`(s0 \ { s1 })), (c3 `(s0 \ { s1 })), hs0 = c0)
  fveq1d((mrCls ` hs0), (s0 \ { s1 }), c3, hs0 = c0)
  syl6eqr((mrCls ` hs0), c3, (mrCls ` c0), hs0 = c0)
  fveq2(hs0, c0, cmrc)
  df-mri(hs0, s0, s1)
  rabex(s0, P(‚ãÉ hs0), ‚àÄ(s1 ‚àà s0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà((mrCls ` hs0)`(s0 \ { s1 }))))
  pwex(‚ãÉ hs0)
  vuniex(hs0)
  rabeqdv(s0, P(‚ãÉ c0), P(c1), c0 ‚àà(Moore ` c1), ‚àÄ(s1 ‚àà s0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà(c3 `(s0 \ { s1 }))))
  pweqd(‚ãÉ c0, c1, c0 ‚àà(Moore ` c1))
  mreuni(c0, c1)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(‚ãÉ ran(Moore))
  diff.hs0.c({ s0 ‚àà P(‚ãÉ c0)| ‚àÄ(s1 ‚àà s0, ¬¨ s1 ‚àà(c3 `(s0 \ { s1 })))})
  diff.cpw.s(s0, ‚ãÉ hs0)
  diff.cuni.s(s0, hs0)
  diff.cpw.s(s0, ‚ãÉ c0)
  diff.cuni.s(s0, c0)

blocks.name: ismri
blocks.content: Criterion for a set to be an independent set of a Moore system. (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)
blocks.origin:
thm ismri(setvar s0, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4) {
  |- wi(wcel(c0, cfv(cmre, c1)), wb(wcel(c2, c3), wa(wss(c2, c1), wral(s0, c2, wn(wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(c2, csn(cv(s0))))))))))
  -| wceq(c4, cfv(cmrc, c0))
  -| wceq(c3, cfv(cmri, c0))
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s0, c2)
} = {
  bitrd(wcel(c0, cfv(cmre, c1)), wcel(c2, c3), wa(wss(c2, c1), wral(s0, c2, wn(wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(c2, csn(cv(s0)))))))), wa(wcel(c2, cpw(c1)), wral(s0, c2, wn(wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(c2, csn(cv(s0)))))))))
  syl6bb(wcel(c0, cfv(cmre, c1)), wcel(c2, c3), wa(wcel(c2, cpw(c1)), wral(s0, c2, wn(wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(c2, csn(cv(s0)))))))), wcel(c2, crab(hs0, cpw(c1), wral(s0, cv(hs0), wn(wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(cv(hs0), csn(cv(s0))))))))))
  eleq2d(c2, c3, crab(hs0, cpw(c1), wral(s0, cv(hs0), wn(wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(cv(hs0), csn(cv(s0)))))))), wcel(c0, cfv(cmre, c1)))
  mrisval(hs0, s0, c0, c1, c3, c4)
  elrab(hs0, c2, cpw(c1), wral(s0, cv(hs0), wn(wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(cv(hs0), csn(cv(s0))))))), wral(s0, c2, wn(wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(c2, csn(cv(s0))))))))
  raleqbi1dv(s0, cv(hs0), c2, wn(wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(cv(hs0), csn(cv(s0)))))), wn(wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(c2, csn(cv(s0)))))))
  notbid(wceq(cv(hs0), c2), wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(cv(hs0), csn(cv(s0))))), wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(c2, csn(cv(s0))))))
  eleq2d(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(cv(hs0), csn(cv(s0)))), cfv(c4, cdif(c2, csn(cv(s0)))), wceq(cv(hs0), c2))
  fveq2d(c4, cdif(cv(hs0), csn(cv(s0))), cdif(c2, csn(cv(s0))), wceq(cv(hs0), c2))
  difeq1(cv(hs0), c2, csn(cv(s0)))
  anbi1d(wcel(c0, cfv(cmre, c1)), wcel(c2, cpw(c1)), wral(s0, c2, wn(wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(c2, csn(cv(s0))))))), wss(c2, c1))
  syl(wcel(c0, cfv(cmre, c1)), wb(wcel(c2, cpw(c1)), wss(c2, c1)), wcel(c1, universe))
  elfvex(c0, cmre, c1)
  elpw2g(c1, universe, c2)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c1)
  diff.hs0.c(c2)
  diff.hs0.c(cpw(c1))
  diff.hs0.w(wral(s0, c2, wn(wcel(cv(s0), cfv(c4, cdif(c2, csn(cv(s0))))))))
  diff.cv.s(s0, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s0, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s0)
}

thm ismri(setvar s0, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4) {
  ‚ä¢ (c0 ‚àà(Moore ` c1)‚Üí(c2 ‚àà c3 ‚Üî(c2 ‚äÜ c1 ‚àß ‚àÄ(s0 ‚àà c2, ¬¨ s0 ‚àà(c4 `(c2 \ { s0 }))))))
  ‚ä£ c4 =(mrCls ` c0)
  ‚ä£ c3 =(mrInd ` c0)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, c0)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, c2)
} = {
  bitrd(c0 ‚àà(Moore ` c1), c2 ‚àà c3, (c2 ‚äÜ c1 ‚àß ‚àÄ(s0 ‚àà c2, ¬¨ s0 ‚àà(c4 `(c2 \ { s0 })))), (c2 ‚àà P(c1)‚àß ‚àÄ(s0 ‚àà c2, ¬¨ s0 ‚àà(c4 `(c2 \ { s0 })))))
  syl6bb(c0 ‚àà(Moore ` c1), c2 ‚àà c3, (c2 ‚àà P(c1)‚àß ‚àÄ(s0 ‚àà c2, ¬¨ s0 ‚àà(c4 `(c2 \ { s0 })))), c2 ‚àà { hs0 ‚àà P(c1)| ‚àÄ(s0 ‚àà hs0, ¬¨ s0 ‚àà(c4 `(hs0 \ { s0 })))})
  eleq2d(c2, c3, { hs0 ‚àà P(c1)| ‚àÄ(s0 ‚àà hs0, ¬¨ s0 ‚àà(c4 `(hs0 \ { s0 })))}, c0 ‚àà(Moore ` c1))
  mrisval(hs0, s0, c0, c1, c3, c4)
  elrab(hs0, c2, P(c1), ‚àÄ(s0 ‚àà hs0, ¬¨ s0 ‚àà(c4 `(hs0 \ { s0 }))), ‚àÄ(s0 ‚àà c2, ¬¨ s0 ‚àà(c4 `(c2 \ { s0 }))))
  raleqbi1dv(s0, hs0, c2, ¬¨ s0 ‚àà(c4 `(hs0 \ { s0 })), ¬¨ s0 ‚àà(c4 `(c2 \ { s0 })))
  notbid(hs0 = c2, s0 ‚àà(c4 `(hs0 \ { s0 })), s0 ‚àà(c4 `(c2 \ { s0 })))
  eleq2d(s0, (c4 `(hs0 \ { s0 })), (c4 `(c2 \ { s0 })), hs0 = c2)
  fveq2d(c4, (hs0 \ { s0 }), (c2 \ { s0 }), hs0 = c2)
  difeq1(hs0, c2, { s0 })
  anbi1d(c0 ‚àà(Moore ` c1), c2 ‚àà P(c1), ‚àÄ(s0 ‚àà c2, ¬¨ s0 ‚àà(c4 `(c2 \ { s0 }))), c2 ‚äÜ c1)
  syl(c0 ‚àà(Moore ` c1), (c2 ‚àà P(c1)‚Üî c2 ‚äÜ c1), c1 ‚àà ùïå)
  elfvex(c0, cmre, c1)
  elpw2g(c1, universe, c2)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c1)
  diff.hs0.c(c2)
  diff.hs0.c(P(c1))
  diff.hs0.w(‚àÄ(s0 ‚àà c2, ¬¨ s0 ‚àà(c4 `(c2 \ { s0 }))))
  diff.cv.s(s0, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s0, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s0)
}

blocks.content: Consequence of a set in a Moore system being independent. Deduction form. (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)

thm ismri2dad(class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, class c5, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wn(wcel(c0, cfv(c1, cdif(c2, csn(c0))))))
  -| wceq(c1, cfv(cmrc, c3))
  -| wceq(c4, cfv(cmri, c3))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c3, cfv(cmre, c5)))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c2, c4))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c0, c2))
} = {
  mpd(w0, wn(wcel(c0, cfv(c1, cdif(c2, csn(c0))))), wral(hs0, c2, wn(wcel(cv(hs0), cfv(c1, cdif(c2, csn(cv(hs0))))))))
  mpbid(w0, wral(hs0, c2, wn(wcel(cv(hs0), cfv(c1, cdif(c2, csn(cv(hs0))))))), wcel(c2, c4))
  ismri2d(hs0, c2, c4, c1, c3, c5, w0)
  mrissd(c2, c5, c4, c3, w0)
  rspcdv(hs0, c2, c0, w0, wn(wcel(cv(hs0), cfv(c1, cdif(c2, csn(cv(hs0)))))), wn(wcel(c0, cfv(c1, cdif(c2, csn(c0))))))
  notbid(wa(w0, wceq(cv(hs0), c0)), wcel(cv(hs0), cfv(c1, cdif(c2, csn(cv(hs0))))), wcel(c0, cfv(c1, cdif(c2, csn(c0)))))
  eleq12d(cv(hs0), cfv(c1, cdif(c2, csn(cv(hs0)))), c0, cfv(c1, cdif(c2, csn(c0))), wa(w0, wceq(cv(hs0), c0)))
  fveq2d(c1, cdif(c2, csn(cv(hs0))), cdif(c2, csn(c0)), wa(w0, wceq(cv(hs0), c0)))
  difeq2d(c2, csn(cv(hs0)), csn(c0), wa(w0, wceq(cv(hs0), c0)))
  sneqd(cv(hs0), c0, wa(w0, wceq(cv(hs0), c0)))
  simpr(w0, wceq(cv(hs0), c0))
  diff.hs0.c(c2)
  diff.hs0.c(c3)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.w(w0)
  diff.hs0.w(wn(wcel(c0, cfv(c1, cdif(c2, csn(c0))))))
}

thm ismri2dad(class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, class c5, wff w0) {
  ‚ä¢ (w0 ‚Üí ¬¨ c0 ‚àà(c1 `(c2 \ { c0 })))
  ‚ä£ c1 =(mrCls ` c3)
  ‚ä£ c4 =(mrInd ` c3)
  ‚ä£ (w0 ‚Üí c3 ‚àà(Moore ` c5))
  ‚ä£ (w0 ‚Üí c2 ‚àà c4)
  ‚ä£ (w0 ‚Üí c0 ‚àà c2)
} = {
  mpd(w0, ¬¨ c0 ‚àà(c1 `(c2 \ { c0 })), ‚àÄ(hs0 ‚àà c2, ¬¨ hs0 ‚àà(c1 `(c2 \ { hs0 }))))
  mpbid(w0, ‚àÄ(hs0 ‚àà c2, ¬¨ hs0 ‚àà(c1 `(c2 \ { hs0 }))), c2 ‚àà c4)
  ismri2d(hs0, c2, c4, c1, c3, c5, w0)
  mrissd(c2, c5, c4, c3, w0)
  rspcdv(hs0, c2, c0, w0, ¬¨ hs0 ‚àà(c1 `(c2 \ { hs0 })), ¬¨ c0 ‚àà(c1 `(c2 \ { c0 })))
  notbid((w0 ‚àß hs0 = c0), hs0 ‚àà(c1 `(c2 \ { hs0 })), c0 ‚àà(c1 `(c2 \ { c0 })))
  eleq12d(hs0, (c1 `(c2 \ { hs0 })), c0, (c1 `(c2 \ { c0 })), (w0 ‚àß hs0 = c0))
  fveq2d(c1, (c2 \ { hs0 }), (c2 \ { c0 }), (w0 ‚àß hs0 = c0))
  difeq2d(c2, { hs0 }, { c0 }, (w0 ‚àß hs0 = c0))
  sneqd(hs0, c0, (w0 ‚àß hs0 = c0))
  simpr(w0, hs0 = c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c2)
  diff.hs0.c(c3)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.w(w0)
  diff.hs0.w(¬¨ c0 ‚àà(c1 `(c2 \ { c0 })))
}

blocks.name: mrieqvd
blocks.content: In a Moore system, a set is independent if and only if, for all elements of the set, the closure of the set with the element removed is unequal to the closure of the original set. Part of Proposition 4.1.3 in [FaureFrolicher] p. 83. (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)

thm mrieqvd(setvar s0, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, wff w0) {

blocks.name: mrieqv2d
blocks.content: In a Moore system, a set is independent if and only if all its proper subsets have closure properly contained in the closure of the set. Part of Proposition 4.1.3 in [FaureFrolicher] p. 83. (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)

blocks.name: mrissmrcd
blocks.content: In a Moore system, if an independent set is between a set and its closure, the two sets are equal (since the two sets must have equal closures by ~ mressmrcd , and so are equal by ~ mrieqv2d .) (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)
blocks.origin:
thm mrissmrcd(class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, class c5, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wceq(c0, c1))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c2, cfv(cmre, c3)))
  -| wceq(c4, cfv(cmrc, c2))

  -| wi(w0, wss(c0, cfv(c4, c1)))

  -| wi(w0, wcel(c0, c5))
} = {
  eqcomd(c0, c1, w0)
  mpd(w0, wceq(c1, c0), wn(wpss(c1, c0)))
  mtod(w0, wpss(c1, c0), wpss(cfv(c4, c1), cfv(c4, c0)))
  syl(w0, wn(wpss(cfv(c4, c1), cfv(c4, c0))), wceq(cfv(c4, c0), cfv(c4, c1)))

  necon2bi(cfv(c4, c0), cfv(c4, c1), wpss(cfv(c4, c1), cfv(c4, c0)))

  mpd(w0, wi(wpss(c1, c0), wpss(cfv(c4, c1), cfv(c4, c0))), wal(hs0, wi(wpss(cv(hs0), c0), wpss(cfv(c4, cv(hs0)), cfv(c4, c0)))))
  mpbid(w0, wal(hs0, wi(wpss(cv(hs0), c0), wpss(cfv(c4, cv(hs0)), cfv(c4, c0)))), wcel(c0, c5))
  mrieqv2d(hs0, c0, c5, c4, c2, c3, w0)
  mrissd(c0, c3, c5, c2, w0)
  spcdv(hs0, c1, universe, w0, wi(wpss(cv(hs0), c0), wpss(cfv(c4, cv(hs0)), cfv(c4, c0))), wi(wpss(c1, c0), wpss(cfv(c4, c1), cfv(c4, c0))))
  ssexd(c1, c0, c5, w0)

  psseq1d(cfv(c4, cv(hs0)), cfv(c4, c0), cfv(c4, c1), wa(w0, wceq(cv(hs0), c1)))
  fveq2d(c4, cv(hs0), c1, wa(w0, wceq(cv(hs0), c1)))
  simpr(w0, wceq(cv(hs0), c1))
  ord(w0, wpss(c1, c0), wceq(c1, c0))

blocks.content: In a Moore system, subsets of independent sets are independent. (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)

} = {
  ismri2dd(hs0, c0, c1, c4, c2, c3, w0)

  mpd(w0, wral(hs0, c0, wn(wcel(cv(hs0), cfv(c4, cdif(c0, csn(cv(hs0))))))), wral(hs0, c5, wn(wcel(cv(hs0), cfv(c4, cdif(c5, csn(cv(hs0))))))))

  imim12d(w0, wcel(cv(hs0), c5), wn(wcel(cv(hs0), cfv(c4, cdif(c5, csn(cv(hs0)))))), wcel(cv(hs0), c0), wn(wcel(cv(hs0), cfv(c4, cdif(c0, csn(cv(hs0)))))))

blocks.name: mreexd
blocks.content: In a Moore system, the closure operator is said to have the _exchange property_ if, for all elements ` y ` and ` z ` of the base set and subsets ` S ` of the base set such that ` z ` is in the closure of ` ( S u. { y } ) ` but not in the closure of ` S ` , ` y ` is in the closure of ` ( S u. { z } ) ` (Definition 3.1.9 in [FaureFrolicher] p. 57 to 58.) This theorem allows us to construct substitution instances of this definition. (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)
blocks.origin:
thm mreexd(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, class c5, wff w0) {

blocks.name: mreexmrid
blocks.content: In a Moore system whose closure operator has the exchange property, if a set is independent and an element is not in its closure, then adding the element to the set gives another independent set. Lemma 4.1.5 in [FaureFrolicher] p. 84. (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)

blocks.name: mreexexd
blocks.content: Exchange-type theorem. In a Moore system whose closure operator has the exchange property, if ` F ` and ` G ` are disjoint from ` H ` , ` ( F u. H ) ` is independent, ` F ` is contained in the closure of ` ( G u. H ) ` , and either ` F ` or ` G ` is finite, then there is a subset ` q ` of ` G ` equinumerous to ` F ` such that ` ( q u. H ) ` is independent. This implies the case of Proposition 4.2.1 in [FaureFrolicher] p. 86 where either ` ( A \ B ) ` or ` ( B \ A ) ` is finite. The theorem is proven by induction using ~ mreexexlem3d for the base case and ~ mreexexlem4d for the induction step. (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.) Remove dependencies on ~ ax-rep and ~ ax-ac2 . (Revised by Brendan Leahy, 2-Jun-2021.)

blocks.name: mreexdomd
blocks.content: In a Moore system whose closure operator has the exchange property, if ` S ` is independent and contained in the closure of ` T ` , and either ` S ` or ` T ` is finite, then ` T ` dominates ` S ` . This is an immediate consequence of ~ mreexexd . (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)

blocks.name: mreexfidimd
blocks.content: In a Moore system whose closure operator has the exchange property, if two independent sets have equal closure and one is finite, then they are equinumerous. Proven by using ~ mreexdomd twice. This implies a special case of Theorem 4.2.2 in [FaureFrolicher] p. 87. (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)
blocks.origin:
thm mreexfidimd(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, class c5, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wbr(c0, cen, c1))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c2, cfv(cmre, c3)))
  -| wceq(c4, cfv(cmrc, c2))
  -| wceq(c5, cfv(cmri, c2))
  -| wi(w0, wral(s0, cpw(c3), wral(s1, c3, wral(s2, cdif(cfv(c4, cun(cv(s0), csn(cv(s1)))), cfv(c4, cv(s0))), wcel(cv(s1), cfv(c4, cun(cv(s0), csn(cv(s2)))))))))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c0, c5))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c1, c5))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c0, cfn))
  -| wi(w0, wceq(cfv(c4, c0), cfv(c4, c1)))
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffss(s0, s2)
  -| diffss(s1, s2)
  -| diffsc(s0, c3)
  -| diffsc(s0, c4)
  -| diffsc(s0, c5)
  -| diffsc(s1, c3)
  -| diffsc(s1, c4)
  -| diffsc(s1, c5)
  -| diffsc(s2, c3)
  -| diffsc(s2, c4)
  -| diffsc(s2, c5)
  -| diffsw(s0, w0)
  -| diffsw(s1, w0)
  -| diffsw(s2, w0)
} = {
  syl2anc(w0, wbr(c0, cen, c1), wbr(c0, cdom, c1), wbr(c1, cdom, c0))
  mreexdomd(s0, s1, s2, c0, c1, c2, c3, c4, c5, w0)
  sseqtrd(c0, cfv(c4, c1), cfv(c4, c0), w0)

  orcd(w0, wcel(c0, cfn), wcel(c1, cfn))

  sbth(c0, c1)
}
